	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64320347"><p>Can I mine the White House lawn? It's not my property, but my neighbor Mike said he didn't care if I did it.</p><p>On what authority does the US government have to determine ownership, rights, or even to resolve disputes of celestial bodies? The Outer Space Treaty isn't sufficient to grant recognizable authority to the US government. So I fail to see how any of this is legal or in line with other international behavior. (<a href="https://www.iflscience.com/who-owns-space-us-asteroid-mining-act-dangerous-and-potentially-illegal-32310" title="iflscience.com">probably illegal<span class="substr"> </span></a> [iflscience.com])</p><p>I hope the International community comes down hard on our stupidity. As a cit</p></div>
